#include <unistd.h>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <sys/wait.h>
#include <fcntl.h>


int main() {
    int pipefd[2];

    if (pipe(pipefd) == -1) {
        perror("pipe");
    }

    // producer
    pid_t pid_p = fork();
    if (pid_p == 0) {
        dup2(pipefd[1], 1);
        close(pipefd[0]); //      

        printf("Hello!!!\n");
        printf("I am writing to stdout!!!\n");

        _exit(0);
    } else if (pid_p < 0) {
        perror("producer");
    }

    // consumer
    pid_t pid_c = fork();
    if (pid_c == 0) {
        dup2(pipefd[0], 0);
        close(pipefd[1]); //       ()

        execlp("cat", "cat", NULL);
    } else if (pid_c < 0) {
        perror("consumer");
    }

    //  !
    close(pipefd[0]);
    close(pipefd[1]);

    // 
    waitpid(pid_p, NULL, 0);
    waitpid(pid_c, NULL, 0);
}


























$ gcc main.c
$ ./a.out
